{{Infobox nonprofit|name=Love for the Elderly|founder=[[Jacob Cramer]]|headquarters=[[Cleveland, OH]]|status=[[501(c)(3)]]|website=[http://lovefortheelderly.org lovefortheelderly.org]|founded=December 2013|purpose=Humanitarian/Activism}}
'''Love for the Elderly''' is a 501(c)(3) [[nonprofit organization]] with volunteers from 56 countries that "strives to bring love and kindness to our elders."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lovefortheelderly.org/|title=Love for the Elderly|website=Love for the Elderly|access-date=2017-01-08}}</ref>
== History == When founder [[Jacob Cramer]]'s grandfather died following a drawn-out battle with lung cancer in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|title=Romona's Kids|url=http://www.cleveland19.com/story/26398692/romonas-kids-love-for-the-elderly|website=Cleveland 19 News|publisher=WOIO|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref> Cramer was profoundly affected, as their relationship had been very strong.<ref>{{Citation|last=TEDx Talks|title=14 Year Old Starts Movement to Touch the Lives of the Elderly {{!}} Jacob Cramer {{!}} TEDxYouth@Cincinnati|date=2015-09-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ayOmOaXC0Z0|accessdate=2017-01-12}}</ref> Motivated by his grief to do something to make a difference in his grandfather's honor, Cramer, 13, began handwriting simple letters of kindness to send to seniors in nursing homes, which would eventually become his Letters of Love program, which has collected and distributed over 25,000 handwritten letters to lonely seniors.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://parade.com/529572/lharris-2/letters-of-hope-how-one-teen-spreads-smiles-to-the-elderly/|title=Letters of Hope – How One Teen Spreads Smiles to the Elderly|last=Harris|first=Lauren|work=Parade|access-date=2017-03-05|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.good-deeds-day.org/blog/good-old-fashioned-letters-are-putting-smiles-on-seniors-faces/|title=Good Old Fashioned Letters Are Putting Smiles on Seniors' Faces - Good Deeds Day|date=2016-02-07|newspaper=Good Deeds Day|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref> Over the past three years, Love for the Elderly has grown internationally, with the sole mission of eponymously providing "love for the elderly."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fetzer.org/blog/teen-invites-us-show-love-elderly|title=Teen Invites Us to Show Love for the Elderly|website=fetzer.org|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>
== Press == Cramer's nonprofit has garnered significant media coverage, particularly in recent years, like [[The Chive]],<ref>{{cite web|title=The Chive|url=http://thechive.com/2014/08/14/and-then-a-hero-comes-along-13-photos/|website=The Chive|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref> and the [[Cleveland Jewish News]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Cleveland Jewish News|url=http://www.clevelandjewishnews.com/news/local_news/pepper-pike-teen-shows-love-for-the-elderly-on-tv/article_15adaad6-c220-11e6-acb1-8ffd8a3e8651.html|website=Cleveland Jewish News|publisher=CJN|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref> Projecting Love for the Elderly into the international spotlight even further, the organization was featured on the cover of [https://web.archive.org/web/20170108192305/http://www.rochsent.com/ftp/American%20Profile/AP20161217.pdf American Profile] in 2016. Directly after this, their inclusion in [[Glamour (magazine)|GLAMOUR]] Magazine's 31 days of kindness alongside other notable nonprofits like [[Oxfam]] and [[One.org]]<ref>{{cite web|title=GLAMOUR Magazine feature|url=http://www.glamour.com/story/non-profit-organizations-to-support-during-the-holidays|website=Glamour|publisher=Condé Nast|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref> was critically received by the public. They were covered by [[Rede Record]] – the 5th largest TV network in the world – for their humanitarian work in Brazil.<ref>{{Citation|last=Love For The Elderly|title=Brazil Students Pen-Palled USA Seniors. This is what happened.|date=2017-03-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qs6MFvumGBk|accessdate=2017-03-05}}</ref>
In 2016, founder Jacob Cramer spoke on national daytime talk show [[Harry (talk show)|HARRY]] <ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Citation|last=Love For The Elderly|title=HARRY Show w/ Harry Connick Jr: "Super Teens" Segment|date=2016-12-31|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qir6ErT4FpY|accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref> on behalf of his global organization's initiatives.
== World Kindness Movement == In 2015, Love for the Elderly joined the 4 largest kindness-centered nonprofits in the USA, becoming one of the 5 USA-based members of the [[World Kindness Movement]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Kindness Movement USA|url=http://www.theworldkindnessmovement.org/member_nation/world-kindness-usa/|website=World Kindness Movement|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref>
