{{Infobox criminal | name = Richard R. Lavigne | image_name = | image_size = 150px | image_caption = mug shot of Lavigne | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1941}} | birth_place = [[United States]] | death_date = | death_place = | alias = | conviction = child sexual abuse | conviction_penalty = | conviction_status = released | occupation = former Catholic priest | spouse = | parents = | children = }} '''Richard Roger Lavigne''' (born 1941)<ref name="flyer">{{cite web |url=http://sorb.chs.state.ma.us/ResultDetail.asp?btn752=Detail |title=Level 3 Sex Offender - Richard Roger Lavigne|publisher=Commonwealth of Massachusetts Sex Offender Registry Board |accessdate=February 14, 2010 }}</ref> is a former priest of the [[Roman Catholic]] [[Diocese of Springfield in Massachusetts]]. Lavigne has been at the center of the [[priest abuse scandal]] in the [[Diocese of Springfield in Massachusetts]] with about 40 claims of [[sexual abuse]] of minors placed against him.
He was removed from ministry by Bishop John Marshall in 1991. He pleaded guilty to two counts of child sexual abuse on June 26, 1992<ref name="flyer"/> and was the only suspect named in the unsolved 1972 murder of 13-year-old Danny Croteau of [[Springfield, Massachusetts]]. In 1994, [[DNA]] tests failed to link Lavigne to the Croteau murder and the [[Hampden County, Massachusetts|Hampden County]] District Attorney [[William Bennett]] did not bring any charges against Lavigne in that case. Lavigne was removed from the ranks of the clergy by the [[Holy See|Vatican]] on 20 November 2003.<ref name=snap>{{cite news|url=http://www.snapnetwork.org/news/otherstates/ma_vatican_defrocks_lavigne.htm|title=Vatican defrocks Lavigne, Springfield, MA Priest |last=Zajac|first=Bill|date=January 21, 2004|work=Springfield Republican|publisher=SNAP|accessdate=2009-04-22}}</ref> Lavigne has [[Sex offender registries in the United States|registered as a sex offender]] and currently resides in [[Chicopee, Massachusetts]].<ref name="flyer"/>
